"Badlington","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably an altered form of English   Waddington   or   Watlington  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Waddington","meanings":["English (Yorkshire and Lancashire): habitational name mostly from Waddington in Yorkshire, but also from Waddington in Lincolnshire and perhaps occasionally Waddington in Coulsdon (Surrey). The first two placenames derive from the Old English personal name <i>Wada</i> + Old English connective <i>-ing-</i> + <i>tūn</i> ‘farmstead, estate’. The Surrey placename derives from Old English <i>hwǣte</i> ‘wheat’, later <i>hwǣten</i> ‘growing with wheat’ + <i>dūn</i> ‘hill’."]}]},{"name":"Robert","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["One of the many French names of Germanic origin that were introduced into Britain by the Normans; it has since remained in continuous use. It is derived from the nearly synonymous elements <i>hrōd</i> ‘fame’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’, and had a native Old English predecessor of similar form (<i>Hreodbeorht</i>), which was supplanted by the Norman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705195,"age":25,"year":"1382","julianDay":2225826,"title":"Wycliffe's Bible","description":"John Wycliffe, English theologian and professor at the University of Oxford, completed a translation of the Bible from the Latin Vulgate into Middle English. This translation is known as Wycliffe's Bible and was completed around 1382.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wycliffe%27s_Bible","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Wycliffe's Bible","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Robert Badlington was born in 1357, in Thame, Oxfordshire, England, his father, Sir Thomas Badlington x, was 19 and his mother, Anne d'Anvers, was 17. He married Polly Babcock. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. He died in 1430, in his hometown, at the age of 73."},"et":{"1357–1430":"1357–1430","1360–1440":"1360–1440","1387–1430":"1387–1430","1338–Male":"1338–Surnud","1340–Female":"1340–Surnud","1338":"1338","1357":"1357","1356":"1356","1387":"1387","1430":"1430","1440":"1440","1340":"1340","1382":"1382","1360":"1360","Thame, Oxfordshire, England":"Thame, Oxfordshire, England","Wycombe, Buckinghamshire, England":"Wycombe, Buckinghamshire, England","Oxfordshire, England":"Oxfordshire, England"},"fi":{"1357–1430":"1357–1430","1360–1440":"1360–1440","1387–1430":"1387–1430","1338–Male":"1338–Kuollut","1340–Female":"1340–Kuollut","1338":"1338","1357":"1357","1356":"1356","1387":"1387","1430":"1430","1440":"1440","1340":"1340","1382":"1382","1360":"1360","Thame, Oxfordshire, England":"Thame, Oxfordshire, England","Wycombe, Buckinghamshire, England":"Wycombe, Buckinghamshire, England","Oxfordshire, England":"Oxfordshire, England"},"fr":{"1357–1430":"1357–1430","1360–1440":"1360–1440","1387–1430":"1387–1430","1338–Male":"1338–Décédé","1340–Female":"1340–Décédée","1338":"1338","1357":"1357","1356":"1356","1387":"1387","1430":"1430","1440":"1440","1340":"1340","1382":"1382","1360":"1360","Thame, Oxfordshire, England":"Thame, Oxfordshire, Angleterre","Wycombe, Buckinghamshire, England":"Wycombe, Buckinghamshire, Angleterre","Oxfordshire, England":"Oxfordshire, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Lorsque Robert Badlington est né en 1357, à Thame, Oxfordshire, Angleterre, son père, Sir Thomas Badlington x, avait 19 ans et sa mère, Anne d'Anvers, avait 17 ans. Il a épousé Polly Babcock. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fille. Il est décédé en 1430, dans sa ville natale, à l’âge de 73 ans."},"de":{"1357–1430":"1357–1430","1360–1440":"1360–1440","1387–1430":"1387–1430","1338–Male":"1338–Verstorben","1340–Female":"1340–Verstorben","1338":"1338","1357":"1357","1356":"1356","1387":"1387","1430":"1430","1440":"1440","1340":"1340","1382":"1382","1360":"1360","Thame, Oxfordshire, England":"Thame, Oxfordshire, England","Wycombe, Buckinghamshire, England":"Wycombe, Buckinghamshire, England","Oxfordshire, England":"Oxfordshire, England","lifeSummary":"Als Robert Badlington 1357 in Thame, Oxfordshire, England geboren wurde, war sein Vater Sir Thomas Badlington x 19 und seine Mutter Anne d'Anvers 17. Er hat Polly Babcock geheiratet. Sie hatten mindestens 1 Tochter. Er starb 1430 im Alter von 73 Jahren in seinem Geburtsort."},"ht":{"1357–1430":"1357–1430","1360–1440":"1360–1440","1387–1430":"1387–1430","1338–Male":"1338–Desede","1340–Female":"1340–Desede","1338":"1338","1357":"1357","1356":"1356","1387":"1387","1430":"1430","1440":"1440","1340":"1340","1382":"1382","1360":"1360","Thame, Oxfordshire, England":"Thame, Oxfordshire, England","Wycombe, Buckinghamshire, England":"Wycombe, Buckinghamshire, England","Oxfordshire, England":"Oxfordshire, England"},"hu":{"1357–1430":"1357–1430","1360–1440":"1360–1440","1387–1430":"1387–1430","1338–Male":"1338–elhunyt","1340–Female":"1340–elhunyt","1338":"1338","1357":"1357","1356":"1356","1387":"1387","1430":"1430","1440":"1440","1340":"1340","1382":"1382","1360":"1360","Thame, Oxfordshire, England":"Thame, Oxfordshire, England","Wycombe, Buckinghamshire, England":"Wycombe, Buckinghamshire, England","Oxfordshire, England":"Oxfordshire, England"},"id":{"1357–1430":"1357–1430","1360–1440":"1360–1440","1387–1430":"1387–1430","1338–Male":"1338–Telah Meninggal","1340–Female":"1340–Telah Meninggal","1338":"1338","1357":"1357","1356":"1356","1387":"1387","1430":"1430","1440":"1440","1340":"1340","1382":"1382","1360":"136